Instead of introducing a new method, I was thinking more like:
if (mMountTable.isMountPoint(childPath.getUri())) {
  mMountTable.checkUnderWritableMountPoint(childPath.getUri());
}

This would allow not creating a new method, and also, this performs the (potentially expensive) check for only the mount point paths.
What do you think?

